 of technology to enhance instruction and improve student learning    Provide technology training and consultation to assist faculty in their teaching and research    Contribute to educational success through the application of advanced technology skills  understanding instructional needs  and application of software and hardware solutions    Supervise  train  and schedule student assistants to ensure knowledgeable  customer oriented service  Qualifications  Master s degree in instructional design  instructional technology  education or a related field  At least three years of experience working at an institute of higher education  expertise with a learning management system  LMS  experience working with faculty one on one or in a group  experience designing and leading training workshops  expertise in the creation of instructional content using digital tools  proven ability to work well in a team environment  demonstrated creativity and problem solving skills  excellent oral and written communication skills  The successful candidate will be a creative thinker and energetic collaborator with a strong interest in helping faculty transform their teaching and assist them in technology based learning solutions to enhance student learning  The ability to be professionally engaged in learning new technologies is essential  Candidates must apply on line at  http virginiajobs peopleadmin com postings 30341 A complete application will include a letter describing relevant experience  interest in the position  current curriculum vitae  and the name of four references with titles  mailing addresses  business home telephone numbers  and email addresses  Full time position  Salary is commensurate with education and experience and includes a generous benefits package  Applications will be accepted until the position is filled  Candidate screening will begin immediately  In a continuing effort to enrich its academic environment and provide equal educational and employment opportunities  VMI encourages women  minorities  disabled individuals and veterans to apply  AmeriCorps  Peace Corps and other national service alumni are also encouraged to apply  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 